THE STUDENT PILOT RPTD THAT THE AIRPLANE WAS LOW ON FINAL APPCH, AND THAT 
HE APPLIED POWER TO MAINTAIN ALTITUDE. AFTER CROSSING THE RUNWAY THRESHOLD, 
HE REDUCED THE POWER TO IDLE AND LOWERED THE NOSE TO MAINTAIN AIRSPEED. HE 
INITIATED A FLARE PRIOR TO TOUCHDOWN, BUT THE AIRPLANE LANDED HARD IN A 
NOSE-LOW ATTITUDE. THE AIRPLANE BEGAN TO PORPOISE, AND THE NOSE LDG 
GEAR COLLAPSED. THE AIRPLANE SUBSEQUENTLY SKIDDED OFF OF THE SIDE OF 
THE RUNWAY. THE STUDENT PILOT HAD APPROX 14 HRS OF SOLO EXPERIENCE AND WAS 
ENDORSED FOR SOLO FLIGHT. 
